<item>
  <title>Are the Packers better than the Bears?</title>
  <dc:creator>Avery Regier</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/the-packers-are-better-than-the-bears/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>The Green Bay Packers and the Chicago Bears have been known rivals for over a century, which is one of the oldest rivalries in the NFL. The first game they played against each other, the Bears won 20-0 in 1921. Since then, they have played over 200 games against each other, which is also the most-played matchup.</p>
<p>This season, the Packers lost to the Bears two out of the three times they faced head-to-head, which made Packers fans everywhere question if they are the superior team. With several player injuries this season from the Packers, including the star quarterback Jordan Love, it left the fans with a sour taste in their mouth watching the Bears come back from being down with only minutes left in the fourth quarter.</p>
<p>Sports Reference gave numbers for the past 10 years showing the Simple Rating System of all the NFC teams, including teams that have moved from cities and changed names. The SRS rates teams by combining the average rate differential and strength of schedule, measuring how many points better or worse a team is than the average team (0.0).</p>
