<p>Looking at the rating, the Packers, in the past 10 years, have shown a far superior SRS than the Bears and most of the NFC, ranking third highest. While the Bears are ranking third to last. This shows that they have been playing better than not just the Bears, but most of the NFC.</p>
<p>To dive deeper into the NFC, specifically looking at the NFC North, where do the Packers stand offensively?</p>
<p>Yardage is a crucial part of football, not only toward getting touchdowns, but also in determining how many you can get in a play and an attempt. Have the Packers had overall better yardage in the past 10 years, and how do they stand in the NFC North?</p>
