<p>The Packers are leading the charge in not only the yards per play, but also the yards per attempt, showing a strong offense for the team. Now look at where the Bears fall, dead last in the division. Looks like they have some offensive work to do, although these last two matchups against the Packers may show a different case.</p>
<p>Broadening the scale, let’s look at the NFL as a whole. Comparing every team to these rivals.</p>
<p>Turnovers can be a game-changer. Especially in those last crucial minutes, fans are white-knuckling their beverages, and their eyes are locked on the screen. Watching your quarterback throw an interception is gut-wrenching to any football fan, so let’s see what the past 10 years look like for the Packers and the Bears’ turnover percentage.</p>
