<p>The Bears had a rough streak in the 2018 season, peaking at the top of the NFL in turnover percentage, which isn’t necessarily what you want to be at the top of. Their percentage has fluctuated over the years, while the Packers have stayed pretty consistent with a downward slope by the end of the 2025 season.</p>
<p>After this season, it was hard to be a Packers fan, but it is good to know that historically, the Packers have always been better than the Bears. With the draft bringing in fresh bodies, it leaves fans with the question of how the team will look next year. For them, hopefully better than the Bears.</p>



